G = C + EE;

H = D + EE;

O = (A + C)/2;

draw(B--C--D);

draw(B--A--D,dashed);

draw(EE--F--G--H--EE);

draw(A--EE,dashed);

draw(B--F);

draw(C--G);

draw(D--H);

draw(A--C,dashed);

draw(A--O--B);

label("$A$",A,S);

label("$B$",B,W);

label("$C$",C,S);

label("$D$",D,E);

label("$E$",EE,N);

label("$F$",F,W);

label("$G$",G,SW);

label("$H$",H,E);

label("$O$",O,N);

[/asy]

Then $\sin \angle GAC = \frac{GC}{AC} = \frac{GC}{2AO}$.  Since $GC = AB = \sqrt{2} AO$, we have $\sin \angle GAC = \frac{\sqrt{2} AO}{2AO} = \boxed{\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}}$.

